        <h4>Special Guest Speaker</h4>
        <h5>Chris Fabricant, Director of Strategic Litigation, <a href="http://www.innocenceproject.org/Content/Chris_Fabricant.php" target="_blank">Innocence Project</a>, New York, NY<br />
          <span class="style8"><em>Strategically Attacking Junk Science</em></span></h5>
        <p> Mr. Fabricant leads the Strategic Litigation Unit, whose attorneys use the courts strategically to address the leading causes of wrongful conviction, including eyewitness misidentification and the misapplication of forensic sciences. Before joining the Innocence Project, he was a clinical law professor and the director of the Criminal Justice Clinic at the Pace University School of Law. Mr. Fabricant has over a decade of criminal defense experience at the state and federal, trial and appellate levels with The Bronx Defenders and Appellate Advocates. <br />
        </p>
        <p><strong>Friday, December 6<br />
        </strong>Moderated by David McDonald, Attorney, Portland<a href="http://www.hallmarkinns.com/index.asp?property=3&amp;rec_id=38" target="_blank"><br />
        </a></p>
